snippet.textDisplay:
Gulon me rang bhare, baad-e-naubahaar chale
chale bhii aao ki gulshan ka karobaar chale*
Gul- flower
naubahaar= early spring
Gulshan= garden

qafas udaas hai yaro, saba se kuchh to kaho
kahi to bahr-e-Khudaa aaj zikr-e-yaar chale

Qafas= bird's cage/ prison
Saba = wind/ gentle breeze
bahre-Khudaa- for God's sake
zikr-e-yaar- mention of beloved

kabhi to subh tere kunj-e-lab se ho aaghaz
kabhii to shab sar-e-kaakul se mushk-baar chale

kunj= corner
lab= lips
Shab- night 
Aaghaz= start
kaakul= hair
Sar-e-kaakul- tresses
mushk= frangrance
mushk-baar= full of fragrance

bada hai dard kaa rishtaa, ye dil Ghariib sahi
tumhaare naam pe aayenge Ghamgusaar chale

Ghamgusaar= one who consoles 

Jo ham pe guzari so guzari magar shab-e-hijra.
hamare ashk terii aaqibat sanwaar chale

Shab e hijra = night of seperation
Ashk= tears
Aaqibat= end, conclusion, future

huzoor-e-yaar hui daftar-e-junun ki talab
girah me leke girebaan ka taar taar chale

Daftar-e-junun = documentation of infatuation 
Talab=sought/ seek
Girah=knot
Garebaan=collar
Taar=shreds

Maqaam 'Faiz' koii raah me jachaa hii nahi
jo ku-e-yaar se nikale to su-e-daar chale

Maqaam= dwelling 
Jacha= attract, appeal
Koo-e-yaar= lane of beloved
Soo-e-daar= towards death

I hope this may help someone 😊
